Interface TypeFilterProducer<T,D>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of object produced
    D - Type of Object stored in DB field.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Selector<Input<? extends D>>, Targetted<T>, TypeConverter<T,D>, TypeProducer<T,D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMessageHandlerFactory.Status, BasicType, ClassType, DatabasePasswordComposite.PasswordStatus, DynamicFormManager.Status, LogFactory.ItemType, SimpleClassType

    public interface TypeFilterProducer<T,D>
extends TypeProducer<T,D>
    TypeProducer with methods to create Filters. Methods are available to explicitly produce SQL and Accept filters as well as a default Filter.
